



Sir
[New York] Sept. 9th 1775. 9 oClock P.M.



Since the Committee of Safety adjourned this afternoon, I am informed that one parcel of Powder landed at the East End of Long Island belonged at & was sent to New London but that a larger parcel was soon after landed at some small distance and forwarded to the owners in Rhode-IslandI could not be well informed of the Quantity in either parcel; but thot it my Duty to give you this Information; and am most respectfully, your Excellencys most obedient & very humble Servant

John McKesson Secry to the Comme of Safety.

